emerald functioned as a mirror, and the eyes of Beatrice will be
compared precisely to a mirror (vv. 119-122).  This new interpretation
has been put forward by V. Bertolucci Pizzorusso, in ^Studi mediolatini
e volgari~ 17 (1969).'
